HTML

Attributes:
Attributes modify how an HTML element behaves.
<a></a>  is to link antoher link we use "herf" in between to add the link to actually link the website 
LIKE THIS: <a href="https://www.youtube.com">link to youtube</a>
tagret tell whether it opens in noew tab using "_blank": <a href="https://www.youtube.com" target="_blank">link to youtube</a>       "target and herf only work on link "

href = modifies which website is opened when clicking this link
<p></p> is to add a paragraph of text.      

<p> – Defines a paragraph used to display normal blocks of text on a webpage.

<button> – Creates a clickable button used to trigger actions or user interactions.

<a href=""> – Anchor tag used to create hyperlinks that navigate to another page or resource.

target="_blank" – Opens the linked page in a new browser tab.

<style> – Contains CSS rules that define how HTML elements should look.

.subscribe-button – A CSS class that styles the Subscribe button with color, size, and hover behavior.

.join-button – A CSS class that creates an outlined button style commonly used for secondary actions.

.tweet-button – Styles a rounded social-media-style button with bold text and bright color.

class="" – Assigns a CSS class to an HTML element so it can be styled or targeted easily.

background-color – Sets the background color of an element.

color – Defines the text color inside an element.

border – Controls the outline of an element including thickness, style, and color.

height & width – Set the size of buttons and other elements.

border-radius – Rounds the corners of buttons for a smooth UI look.

cursor: pointer – Changes the mouse cursor to indicate the element is clickable.

font-size – Controls how large the text appears.

font-weight – Makes text bold or normal.

font-family – Specifies the font style used for text rendering.

margin / margin-top / margin-left – Adds spacing outside elements to improve layout.

display: block – Forces an element to start on a new line and take full width.

.p1 – Styles the price text to appear bold and green indicating availability.

.p2 – Styles secondary information text like delivery details.

.add-to-cart-button – Styles the Add to Cart button to look like an e-commerce action button.

.buy-now-button – Styles the Buy Now button to highlight immediate purchase action.

⚠️ Important note (README-worthy wisdom):
A <button> cannot contain an <a> tag—use either:

an <a> styled like a button, or

a <button> with JavaScript navigation.
How to use GIT

git init # used to initialize repository

git remote add origin <link of github repository> # used to link github repository with gits local repository

git add <filename> # used to add file for tracking

git commit -m "message here" # used to commit changes for tracking

git push -u origin master # used to push changes to github repository